VERIFIABILITY COMMITMENT

Closed-source does not mean opaque. The claims the Software makes about
its own behavior — cost per message, grounding accuracy, architectural
structure, absence of fabrication — will be cryptographically verifiable
per the Verifiable Claims Roadmap in README.md. Verifiability ships in
phases alongside the hosted tier.

---

FORWARD COMMITMENT TO SOURCE-AVAILABLE RELEASE

This Software will transition to a source-available license under the
following milestone conditions, whichever occurs first:

(a) Monthly revenue from the hosted tier reaches or exceeds 2x monthly
    infrastructure operating costs for three (3) consecutive months; or

(b) Twelve (12) months have elapsed from the date of the first paying
    customer.

At that milestone, this license will be superseded by a source-available
license permitting inspection, modification for self-hosting, and
community contribution — with terms prohibiting (i) closed-source resale
as a premium SaaS product and (ii) stripping of attribution.

This forward commitment is binding and public. It may be accelerated but
not deferred.

